==English==
===Etymology===
from [[Tamil]] paraiyar; 'parai' in Tamil is type of large drum designed to announce king's notices to the public. And the people who made living using the 'parai' are 'paraiyar'; in the caste ridden society they were in lower strata, hence derisively as 'paraiah' and pariah.  Now used to describe an outcast in English; Libya until recently was known as a pariah state; others unwilling to mingle with them.

===Noun===
'''pariah''' ([[pariahs]])

#an [[outcast]]
#a demographic group, species, or community that is generally despised.
#someone in [[exile]]

